dt: {bc}a long-legged, swift-moving cat ({it}Acinonyx jubatus{/it}) about the size of a small leopard with a yellowish to tan coat covered with numerous round to oval black spots and blunt claws that only partially retract and having a current range restricted to Africa and isolated parts of Iran

et: Hindi {it}cītā{/it} & Urdu {it}chītā{/it} leopard, from Sanskrit {it}citraka{/it}, from {it}citra{/it} bright, variegated; akin to Old High German {it}heitar{/it} bright {ma}{mat|-hood|}{/ma}
shortdef: a long-legged, swift-moving cat (Acinonyx jubatus) about the size of a small leopard with a yellowish to tan coat covered with numerous round to oval black spots and blunt claws that only partially retract and having a current range restricted to Africa and isolated parts of Iran
